The ultimate locations of these files are:

dhcpcd.conf - /etc/dhcpcd.conf
hostapd.conf - /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf
default_hostapd - /etc/default/hostapd
dnsmasq.conf - /etc/dnsmasq.conf
rc.local[.aphost][.apclient] - /etc/rc.local

*.aphost denotes files used when in configuration mode
*.apclient denotes files used when in regular use mode


My Notes Below...
Configure the Host AP static IP at:  /etc/dhcpcd.conf
# ONLY FOR HOSTAP SETUP!!!!
interface wlan0
    static ip_address=10.0.0.1/24


---------------------

Configure DHCP SERVER at: /etc/dnsmasq.conf

interface=wlan0      # Use the require wireless interface - usually wlan0
  dhcp-range=10.0.0.2,10.0.0.20,255.255.255.0,24h

---------------------

Add file for HOSTAP: /etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf

interface=wlan0
driver=nl80211
ssid=name of ssid
hw_mode=g
channel=7
# MIGHT be able to use channel 0 for auto channel
wmm_enabled=0
macaddr_acl=0
auth_algs=1
ignore_broadcast_ssid=0
wpa=2
wpa_passphrase=thepasswordforap
wpa_key_mgmt=WPA-PSK
wpa_pairwise=TKIP
rsn_pairwise=CCMP

---------------------

Update: sudo nano /etc/default/hostapd
with:

DAEMON_CONF="/etc/hostapd/hostapd.conf"